<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eggers" authorityYear="1923" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Xyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xyleborus insulindicus" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="insulindicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xyleborus insulindicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Eggers, 1923; original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Large and robust species, 4.1-5.6 mm long, 2.2-2.55
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hulcr &amp; Cognato, 2009" authorityName="Hulcr &amp; Cognato" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Beaverium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Beaverium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Beaverium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the declivity distinctly flattened and posterolaterally broadened, posterolateral declivital margin costate, terminating at interstriae 5; pronotal disc asperate; pronotum anterior margin with continuously elevated carina; scutellum flat, flush with elytra, mycangial tufts absent, and procoxae contiguous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
